data.title: The Busy Executive's Database Guide
data.notes: An overview of available database systems with emphasis on common business applications. Illustrated.

data.title: Cooking with Computers: Surreptitious Balance Sheets
data.notes: Helpful hints on how to use your electronic resources to the best advantage.

data.title: You Can Combat Computer Stress!
data.notes: The latest medical and psychological techniques for living with the electronic office. Easy-to-understand explanations.

data.title: Straight Talk About Computers
data.notes: Annotated analysis of what computers can do for you: a no-hype guide for the critical user.

data.title: Silicon Valley Gastronomic Treats
data.notes: Favorite recipes for quick, easy, and elegant meals.

data.title: The Gourmet Microwave
data.notes: Traditional French gourmet recipes adapted for modern microwave cooking.

data.title: But Is It User Friendly?
data.notes: A survey of software for the naive user, focusing on the 'friendliness' of each.

data.title: Secrets of Silicon Valley
data.notes: Muckraking reporting on the world's largest computer hardware and software manufacturers.

data.title: Computer Phobic AND Non-Phobic Individuals: Behavior Variations
data.notes: A must for the specialist, this book examines the difference between those who hate and fear computers and those who don't.

data.title: Is Anger the Enemy?
data.notes: Carefully researched study of the effects of strong emotions on the body. Metabolic charts included.

data.title: Life Without Fear
data.notes: New exercise, meditation, and nutritional techniques that can reduce the shock of daily interactions. Popular audience. Sample menus included, exercise video available separately.

data.title: Prolonged Data Deprivation: Four Case Studies
data.notes: What happens when the data runs dry?  Searching evaluations of information-shortage effects.

data.title: Emotional Security: A New Algorithm
data.notes: Protecting yourself and your loved ones from undue emotional stress in the modern world. Use of computer and nutritional aids emphasized.

data.title: Onions, Leeks, and Garlic: Cooking Secrets of the Mediterranean
data.notes: Profusely illustrated in color, this makes a wonderful gift book for a cuisine-oriented friend.

data.title: Fifty Years in Buckingham Palace Kitchens
data.notes: More anecdotes from the Queen's favorite cook describing life among English royalty. Recipes, techniques, tender vignettes.

data.title: Sushi, Anyone?
data.notes: Detailed instructions on how to make authentic Japanese sushi in your spare time.
